A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Hattie B. Dorsey; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Hattie B. Dorsey on May 29, 2024; and
4 WHEREAS, Hattie B. Dorsey was a visionary leader and the founding President and CEO
5 of the Atlanta Neighborhood Development Partnership, Inc.;and
6 WHEREAS, she was a tireless advocate for affordable and mixed-income housing, and
7 devoted her life to creating opportunities for families and communities across metro Atlanta;
8 and
9 WHEREAS, throughout her distinguished career, Hattie B. Dorsey broke racial and gender
10 barriers in government and nonprofit leadership, serving in key roles with the United States
11 Department of the Interior, Mayor Ivan Allen, United States Representative Charles Weltner,
12 and the NAACP Legal Defense Fund; and
13 WHEREAS, upon returning to Atlanta in 1984, she served as Vice President of the Atlanta
14 Economic Development Corporation, now Invest Atlanta, where she worked to increase
