15 minority participation in major redevelopment projects and address the decline of historically
16 Black neighborhoods; and
17 WHEREAS, in partnership with civic leaders, she helped establish Atlanta Neighborhood
18 Development Partnership, Inc., and led the organization for 15 years, securing over $15
19 million for community development organizations and launching one of the region's first
20 United States Treasury Certified Development Financial Institutions; and
21 WHEREAS, her work laid the foundation for Atlanta's current housing initiatives and
22 inspired a generation of leaders, as well as left behind a powerful legacy of leadership,
23 compassion, and service; and
24 WHEREAS, she gave inspiration to many through her high ideals, morals, and deep concern
25 for her fellow citizens, and the devotion, patience, and understanding she demonstrated to
26 her family and friends were admired by others; and
27 WHEREAS, she was a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation
28 for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness, and by the example she made of her life,
29 she made this world a better place in which to live; and
30 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous woman, Hattie B. Dorsey will long be
31 remembered for her love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who
32 had the great fortune of knowing her.
33 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
34 join in honoring the life and memory of Hattie B. Dorsey and express their deepest and most
35 sincere regret at her passing.
